<br>
<br>
Actually, the Sleeper himself is effectively impossible to kill - at least in the form he's shown himself in, thus far.<br>
<br>
Aside from his simply disgusting melee output, and his insane AC - he's got an estimated 2,147,483,647 hitpoints. (This is assuming he has the maximum allowed by a 32bit signed integer.) And he deathtouches.<br>
<br>
I'm guessing you're thinking of the 4th warder - Ventani. He's been killed, and it's his death that spawns the sleeper. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
-Daethe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uelaurieldragonstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elauriel Dragonstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 3:27:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Aye, the Sleeper is not killable.  The guild you are thinking of made use of some tricky zone details to fight the 4th warder, who spawns the Sleeper.<br>
<br>
Alas, we will never see him again on Inny. <p><img src ="http://web4.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/86/2369886.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uobeorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Obeorn </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 3:42:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Thanks Daethe and Elauriel, I couldn't remember the details.<br>
<br>
What's in the zone now? Is it bare?  Are the warders gone as well?<br>
<br>
Obeorn Winterstrife<br>
Wanderer of Tunare<br>
Spirit of the Moon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 4:12:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Warders gone, but there are some golems that have the warder loot -- at least the primal, although not the other stuff.<br>
<br>
It's rumored it might be possible to put the sleeper back to sleep.<br>
<br>
Note that you won't find him on our server now.  He's supposedly off bugging Veeshan herself.  So no worries he's going to disrupt your camp...<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uoderrybadgerclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oderry Badgerclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 4:15:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://clanbadgerclaw.homestead.com/files/face.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Three named Golems and yard Trash. The Golems drop Primal weapons for sure, and I &quot;think&quot; they drop priceless weapons  I also &quot;think&quot; the yard trash drops priceless weapons. Also there is a scale that drops for a quest in WW wgich rewards you, after turning the scale and ST key in, with 1 of 5 different items, which you can turn in to the quest guy for one of the other 5 items. You can do that infinit times. Word is that the scale is ultra rare, like 1/1000 golems drop it. As far as i know, AV has one. I don't think TD or LoD got a scale yet.<br>
<br>
As far as the sleeper goes... i don't think anyone that awoke him ever took a serious shot at him. Only GM's and Guides have killed him. In the form of the /target /kill commands. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhellra1ser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HELLRA1SER</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 4:47:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/SelfPortraits/HELLRA1SER.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> I doubt even GMs/Guides would be able to kill him.  I would think that the Sleeper would kill GMs too.  I've seen GMs get killed pretty easily before.  Two noticable times were Sephrena drowning, while heading to a wedding in BB, and Istari getting killed by the Key Master in the PoA, while trying to reset him to sell instead of saying he's not open for business. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwolfypaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wolfypaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ally Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 4:51:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Hellraiser --<br>
<br>
1. Except through bugs, guides and GMs can't take agro.<br>
<br>
2. Guides and GMs have a /kill command that makes a mob go POOF.  No muss, no fuss.  Consider it Gm-Deathtouch.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uoderrybadgerclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oderry Badgerclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 5:15:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://clanbadgerclaw.homestead.com/files/face.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Exactly Wolfy. Once you become a guide and any CS above that you have access to the /kill command. But, every time they use it, they have to report that they used it, why they used it, and why they felt they were left with that choice.<br>
<br>
And yes, Guides/GMs can die. They are set to beta neutral on all NPCs, but they are not immune to drowning, lava, or AoE spells. They do, however, have a right-click item (Earring of Z) that makes them immune to such things. And I am pretty sure that some time withen the last year they recieved an Enduring Breath item, so no more worries of drowning.<br>
<br>
They also never get hunger or thirsty... in game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhellra1ser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HELLRA1SER</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 5:53:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/SelfPortraits/HELLRA1SER.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> Ah.  Thanks for the correction.  It's good to know.  Now that we've changed the thread's topic, I'd like to ask you two if you know what happened in this story about a GM.  During a server crash, GMs were visiting all the zones to ressurect everyone they could and I watched a GM in the basement of Unrest aggroing the whole zone and seeing things run down and die as soon as they attack the GM.  You can say this is a question about GMs aggroing NPCs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uhellra1ser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HELLRA1SER</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 5:54:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hellra1ser.homestead.com/files/SelfPortraits/HELLRA1SER.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> I mean, right after the server crash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uoderrybadgerclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oderry Badgerclaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 6:21:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://clanbadgerclaw.homestead.com/files/face.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> I've never heard of anything like that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umisanthropicmagi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Misanthropic Magi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.stopstart.fsnet.co.uk/smilie/thebirds.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/18/02 6:45:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=968.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sleeper</span><hr size=1> just like w/ anything else in this game, bugs occur.  GMs/Guides take agro from NPCs on occassion whan thay aren't supposed to.  it happens. <p>~Oul<br>
